NAME
    Ballerina OpenApi - Gen Service is a tool which will convert an OpenApi contract to a Ballerina mock service.

    Note: This is an Experimental tool ship under ballerina hence this will only support limited set of functionality.
SYNOPSIS
    ballerina openapi gen-service <module-name>:<service-name> <openapi-contract>
OPTIONS
    module-name
        This option will be used as the module name when the command generate a new module
        for the given openapi contract.
    service-name
        This option will be used as the service name and as the file name of the ballerina
        service file.
    openapi-contract
        This will be the contract file location of the openapi contract which will be
        used to create the ballerina service.
    - h
        providing -h will show the help file for the Ballerina openapi gen-service command.
DEFAULT BEHAVIOR
    If no options or sub commands are given on execution, Ballerina openapi command will show
    the help file for the command.
EXAMPLES
    Get help for Ballerina Gen Service command
    $ ballerina openapi gen-service -h

    Generate a Ballerina module ( petstore ) with a mock service named petstoreservice
    $ ballerina openapi gen-service petstore:petstoreservice petstore.yaml